# VS Code Extension Rules

## Architecture

- Reuse `packages/fiber-rpc`, `packages/diagnostics`, and `packages/shared` — no duplicated RPC logic
- Extension activates on relevant commands/views; keep activation lightweight
- Node URL configurable via VS Code settings (`fiberguard.nodeUrl`)

## Commands & Views

- Tree view for channels/peers; output channel for payment diagnostics
- "Can I Pay?" as a command palette action with input for invoice/amount
- Show diagnostics inline — same messages as web dashboard

## Extension API

- Use `vscode.window.showErrorMessage` with actionable text, not stack traces
- Long-running RPC: progress notification with cancellation where supported
- Never store private keys; read-only diagnostics by default
